messageBody:
I have just uploaded another font. This font is called "kingsley." It
is a revised version of the "kwikskript" font. The only difference
between the two is that "kingsley" looks better on the screen in font
sizes 12 & below. Both fonts appear to print equally well at any font
size. There were also a few tweaks to some of the characters.

As "kingsley" is an all-around better replacement to "kwikskript,"
there is no logical point in downloading both of them unless it is
just to compare the two. I am leaving "kwikskript" up for now & may
later remove it.

I have just uploaded another font. This font is called "kingsley." It
is a revised version of the "kwikskript" font. The only difference
between the two is that "kingsley" looks better on the screen in font
sizes 12 & below. Both fonts appear to print equally well at any font
size. There were also a few tweaks to some of the characters.

As "kingsley" is an all-around better replacement to "kwikskript,"
there is no logical point in downloading both of them unless it is
just to compare the two. I am leaving "kwikskript" up for now & may
later remove it.
